data.name: Blackened Chicken with Spicy Mango Salsa
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy blackened chicken topped with a refreshing spicy mango salsa for a burst of flavor!
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat.
Rub the chicken breasts with olive oil and season generously with Cajun seasoning.
Cook the chicken for about 6-8 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and the juices run clear.
While the chicken cooks, prepare the spicy mango salsa by combining diced mango, red onion, jalapeño, cilantro, lime juice, and salt in a bowl.
Once the chicken is cooked, let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.
Serve the sliced chicken topped with the spicy mango salsa.
data.detailedName: Juicy Blackened Chicken with Refreshing Spicy Mango Salsa
